- 'work-in-progress' represents parts that are in the production process but not yet completed;
- 'produced quantities' represent parts that have been fully produced and are ready for use or sale.

- "garden of production" refers to the total quantity of parts produced;
- "seeds sown in the work-in-progress inventory" refers to the total quantity of parts currently in work-in-progress inventory;
- "blossomed more than" means the total quantity produced is greater than the total work-in-progress quantity.

